1 packet flat noodles
1 bag Chopped Veggie Mix
1 packet beef strips
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet teriyaki sauce
1 packet Crispy Shallots
½ lemon
1 bag Asian Greens
1 packet Ginger & Lemongrass Paste
olive oil

• Boil the kettle
• Heat a saucepan over medium-high heat. Half-fill with boiling water
• Cook flat noodles until tender, 3-4 mins
• In last min of cook time, gently stir noodles with a fork to separate
• Drain, rinse and set aside
• Roughly chop Asian greens and capsicum. Chop carrot into
thin rounds

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over medium heat. Cook capsicum and carrot, 4-5 mins
• Add Asian greens and cook until just wilted, 1-2 mins. Transfer to a bowl. Set aside
• Return pan to high heat with a drizzle of oil. Add beef, garlic paste and ginger lemongrass paste and cook,
tossing, until browned, 1-2 mins. Set aside

• Slice lemon into wedges
• To frying pan, add teriyaki sauce, a splash of water, a squeeze of lemon juice, noodles and veggies
• Toss to combine
• Divide between plates. Serve sprinkled with crispy shallots